show_title: GM Farcaster ep169 Wednesday October 16, 2024 with guest @macbudkowski /kiwi-news
text:
our @kiwi x @nouns writing contest news is out!

Everyone is welcome to write about cc0, decentralized governance, bottom-up brand building and other Nounish subjects.

We prepared five prompts to help authors explore the Nouniverse. We also received a prompt from one of the Nounders - @seneca. To participate in the contest, your blog post must answer at least one of the prompts.

Apart from the eternal glory, you will be able to win a part of the 3.5 ETH prize pool. Our contest is platform agnostic, so you can post your essay anywhere you want - on Paragraph, Mirror, Substack, X, Farcaster, or even ZORA.

Even if you don’t win the main prize, you can win some attention and subscribers because Kiwi and some Nouns members will repost the best submissions.

You can learn more about the contest here:
https://paragraph.xyz/@kiwi-updates/into-the-nouniverse-writing-contest

PS: Thanks to @ccarella.eth, @nounishprof and @wiz, for helping to set it up, and thanks to all Nouns who supported our prop ⌐◨-◨

html.ogDescription: Kiwi runs a writing contest with Nouns. Writers will explore cc0, decentralized governance, bottom-up brand building, and other Noun-ish subjects ⌐◨-◨.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep169 Wednesday October 16, 2024 with guest @macbudkowski /kiwi-news
text:
We're shutting down the x-posting experiment. 

For a few months, we've been testing a feature with a few users to cross posts their tweets from X to Farcaster. 

We're shutting it down because we can't get it to work reliably with the current APIs, and when it fails it's really frustrating for users.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep169 Wednesday October 16, 2024 with guest @macbudkowski /kiwi-news
text:
“isn’t authentic to fc”

it’s a different level of energy here, built on optimism + shared ethos

it’s a different culture here, where real convo + long term mindset win

fc may be *late* to the first wave of social, but reality is it’s first to onchain social, and the shift to ownership just started 🌱

cast.text:
Difference in content types make this really hard to work 100%. 

It's also not achieving the goal of increasing conversations. People who x-post don't use the app any more frequently. People who see x-posts are les likely to engage because the content isn't authentic to FC.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep169 Wednesday October 16, 2024 with guest @macbudkowski /kiwi-news
text:
Looking for feedback on this iteration for channels

The single biggest remaining complaint is people feeling like the pre-existing, large, topic based channels like /food or /founders should be more accesible.

It will also reduce work for channel mods who don't want to have to approve every single person who wants to cast in their channel, but are OK giving up some control of who (and they can always invite someone to be a member to guarantee it).

Curious:

1. Would you turn this on or off for your channel?
2. Any concerns?

show_title: GM Farcaster ep169 Wednesday October 16, 2024 with guest @macbudkowski /kiwi-news
text:
There are no rewards for running hubs. Not today. Not ever. 

Warps do not fluctuate in value. 

Channels are not canonical topics. 

Channels haven’t been decentralized yet. 

DCs are not encrypted. 

2 FIDs can communicate even if they get hidden at the client/app level. 

If you use ENS as your display name, no one can take that away from you. 

Farcaster names and channel names can be taken from you. 

Freedom of speech is something worth fighting for ✊

show_title: GM Farcaster ep169 Wednesday October 16, 2024 with guest @macbudkowski /kiwi-news
text: One thing I respect about Bountycaster, Daylight, Degen, Frens, Farcaster, and a handful of other cryptonative teams building right now is that the entire founding team, not just the ceo, have deep conviction in crypto.

cast.text:
Can’t stop thinking about how bullish i am on the /frens team!

1. They know kpis and have clear but aggressive goals 
2. They know exactly who their users are and are passionate about giving them what they want
3. They’re iterating on the product and growing from 10-100-1000 users that love the app
4. They’re figuring out distribution and know all the levers to pull in different market scenarios

This may seem like simple stuff but it feels incredibly rare in crypto
